                  <additions>
                    <list>
                      <item xml:id="e1">
                        <desc>
                          <locus target="#iv(erso) #2r #103r #103v" facs="002 004 105 106">Fols. iv(erso), 2r, 103r, 103v</locus>: blank except for scrawls
                        </desc>
                      </item>
                      <item xml:id="e2">
                        <desc>
                          Numbered quires: quires 2 and 4–9
                        </desc>
                      </item>

                      <item xml:id="e3">
                        <desc>
                          words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#12r #25v #27v #28v" facs="014 028 030 031">folss. 12r, 25v, 27v, 28v, </locus>, etc.);
                          and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#29r #32r" facs="031 034">29r, 32r, </locus>);
                          erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#26v #42r #42v #87v" facs="029 044 045 090">26v, 42r, 42v, 87v, </locus>, etc.);
                          text has been removed (e.g., <locus target="#27r #55v" facs="029 058">27r, 55v, </locus>).
                          There is an extensive amount of scribal
                          interaction using symbols referring to text in the top margin in at
                          least four distinct scribal hands. First is a hand writing in pencil and
                          the symbol (┴) is used (e.g.<locus target="#3v" facs="006">f. 3v, col. 2, line 3</locus>; <locus target="#4v" facs="007">f. 4v, col. 2, line 7</locus>; <locus target="#5r" facs="007">f. 5r, col. 1, line 9</locus>)
                          and later the symbol (+) is used (e.g., <locus target="#35r" facs="037">, col. 2, line 2</locus>;
                          <locus target="#51v" facs="054">f. 51v, col. 1, line 5</locus>; <locus target="#52r" facs="054">, col. 1, line 3</locus>).
                          Second is a hand in ink pen and
                          the symbol (+) is used (<locus target="#24v" facs="027">f. 24v, col. 1, line 11</locus>; <locus target="#26r" facs="028">f. 26r, col. 1, line 24</locus>).
                          Third is a hand in black ink and the symbol (+) is used (<locus target="#29r" facs="031">f. 29r, col. 1, line 14</locus>; <locus target="#44r" facs="046">f. 44r, col. 1, line 3</locus>).
                          Fourth is another hand in black ink and the symbols (┴ and +) are used (<locus target="#29r" facs="031">f. 29r, col. 2, line 18</locus>;
                          <locus target="#30r" facs="032">f. 30r, col. 1, line 1</locus>; <locus target="#31v" facs="034">f. 31v, col. 1, line 9</locus>).
                           Other instances may point to additional scribal hands (e.g., <locus target="#93v" facs="096">f. 93v,  col. 2, line 20</locus>)
                        </desc>
                      </item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
